<figure class="viz" aria-labelledby="alignment-loop-title">
  <figcaption id="alignment-loop-title">
    Alignment is a control loop, not a single loss function
  </figcaption>

  <div class="loop">
    <section>
      <span>Specify</span>
      <strong>Write the intended behavior</strong>
      <small>principles, examples, policies</small>
    </section>
    <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
    <section>
      <span>Supervise</span>
      <strong>Turn intent into a training signal</strong>
      <small>preferences, critiques, process labels</small>
    </section>
    <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
    <section>
      <span>Optimize</span>
      <strong>Change the model policy</strong>
      <small>SFT, RL, direct preference losses</small>
    </section>
    <i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
    <section>
      <span>Audit</span>
      <strong>Search for hidden failure modes</strong>
      <small>red teams, model organisms, interventions</small>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="return">
    <span>Observed failures revise the specification and supervision</span>
    <span aria-hidden="true">↶</span>
  </div>
</figure>

